<P>In the fir&s;t example here, I begin at the right hand, or pence rank, and &s;ay, 6 and 3 is 9, and 5 is 14, and 4 is 18d. (or 1s. 6d.) I &s;et down 6 under the pence line, and carry 1, for the 1s. to the next rank, and &s;ay, the 1 that I carry and 6 is 7, and 4 is 11, and 2 is 13; I come down the next rank, &s;aying, 13 and 10 is 23, and 10 is 33; here I &s;et down 13 under the &s;hillings line, and carry 1 to the next, or pounds row; again, the 1 that I carry, and 7, is 8, and 9 is 17, and 8
