<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>MULTIPLICATION.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="subsection">
<HEAD>EXAMPLE I.</HEAD>
<P>What amounts 6 yards of cloth to, at 4Dls. 5Dms. 4<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ns
<GAP DESC="math"></P>
<P>I begin at the right hand row here, and &s;ay, 6 times 4 is 24, I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">wn 4 u<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">der the cents row, and carry 2 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">r the 2 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> to the next, or dimes row, then 6 times 5 is 30,
<PB N="270" REF="023387_0272_0FBF652136C92968">
and 2 that I carry is 32, here I &s;et down 2 under the Dimes rank, and carry three for the three tens; la&s;tly, 6 times 4 is 24, and 3 is 27; here the operation is fini&s;hed, and I find the price of the cloth to be, twenty-&s;even Dollars, two Dimes, and four Cents.</P>
</DIV3>
